re\" Founder Thought Leadership: Publish 2 op-eds per quarter in target publications Speak at 4 women's health conferences (Year 1) Launch Second Spring podcast (Month 6) Phase 3: Research Contribution (Year 2+) Original Research Projects: Annual \"State of Menopause\" survey (partner with university) Member data analysis (anonymized, IRB-approved) Product efficacy tracking studies Publish findings in peer-reviewed journals Goal: Become the data source journalists cite for menopause statistics H. INBOUND TRAFFIC STRATEGY The Content Funnel Architecture Top of Funnel: Awareness Content High-Traffic Blog Posts (Target: 10,000+ monthly visitors each) \"47 Perimenopause Symptoms No One Warns You About\" \"Menopause Weight Gain: The Complete Scientific Guide\" \"HRT vs. Non-Hormonal Treatment: Evidence-Based Comparison\" \"The Best Cooling Sheets for Night Sweats (Tested by Real Women)\" \"Menopause and Anxiety: Why It Happens and What Helps\" Lead Magnets: Symptom Tracker (printable PDF) Sleep Restoration Protocol (7-day guide) Supplement Decision Tree (interactive quiz) Doctor Discussion Guide (conversation templates) Menopause Meal Plan (5-day recipes) Middle of Funnel: Consideration Content Interactive Tools: Symptom Severity Quiz - Personalized recommendations HRT Eligibility Calculator - Risk assessment Product Finder - Match symptoms to solutions Cost Savings Calculator - Show ROI of membership Video Content Series: \"Ask the Expert\" - Monthly Q&A with advisory board \"Member Spotlight\" - Transformation stories \"Product Reviews\" - Honest evaluations \"Myth Busting\" - Debunk common misconceptions Bottom of Funnel: Conversion Content Social Proof Assets: 50+ video testimonials Case studies (before/after symptom tracking) Member success metrics dashboard Community highlights reel Trust Builders: Money-back guarantee (30 days) Privacy policy transparency Clinical advisory board bios Evidence-based product vetting process No-spam community guidelines Organic Socia